  "pages": [
    {
      "text": "Jacob loved his son Joseph more than all his other sons.",
      "image": "page-01.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF8E1",
      "accent": "#F9A825",
      "audio": "page-01.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "He made Joseph a beautiful coat with many bright colors.",
      "image": "page-02.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF3E0",
      "accent": "#FB8C00",
      "audio": "page-02.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Joseph's ten older brothers saw the coat and burned with jealousy.",
      "image": "page-03.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#E53935",
      "audio": "page-03.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "One day, the brothers grabbed Joseph and threw him into a deep pit.",
      "image": "page-04.webp",
      "bg": "#EDE7F6",
      "accent": "#6A1B9A",
      "audio": "page-04.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Then they sold Joseph to traders who took him far away to Egypt.",
      "image": "page-05.webp",
      "bg": "#E3F2FD",
      "accent": "#1565C0",
      "audio": "page-05.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "In Egypt, Joseph worked hard, but his master's wife told lies about him.",
      "image": "page-06.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF9C4",
      "accent": "#F57F17",
      "audio": "page-06.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Joseph was thrown into prison, even though he had done nothing wrong.",
      "image": "page-07.webp",
      "bg": "#EFEBE9",
      "accent": "#4E342E",
      "audio": "page-07.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Inside the dark prison, Joseph prayed and trusted that God had not forgotten him.",
      "image": "page-08.webp",
      "bg": "#E8EAF6",
      "accent": "#3949AB",
      "audio": "page-08.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "God gave Joseph the gift of understanding dreams, and word reached Pharaoh.",
      "image": "page-09.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#2E7D32",
      "audio": "page-09.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Joseph told Pharaoh that seven good years and seven hungry years were coming.",
      "image": "page-10.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF8E1",
      "accent": "#F9A825",
      "audio": "page-10.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Pharaoh was amazed and made Joseph the most powerful man in all of Egypt.",
      "image": "page-11.webp",
      "bg": "#FFF3E0",
      "accent": "#E65100",
      "audio": "page-11.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "When famine spread across the land, Joseph's brothers came to Egypt to beg for food.",
      "image": "page-12.webp",
      "bg": "#FCE4EC",
      "accent": "#C62828",
      "audio": "page-12.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "Joseph looked at his brothers and felt tears fill his eyes, but he chose to forgive.",
      "image": "page-13.webp",
      "bg": "#E3F2FD",
      "accent": "#0D47A1",
      "audio": "page-13.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    },
    {
      "text": "God turned Joseph's suffering into a blessing for his whole family and all the people.",
      "image": "page-14.webp",
      "bg": "#E8F5E9",
      "accent": "#1B5E20",
      "audio": "page-14.mp3",
      "timestamps": []
    }
  ]
}